cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with training deep learning models for medical image classification and segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper proposes an active learning framework that involves selecting informative samples, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The framework also uses Bayesian neural networks, which is a popular technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves generating realistic images using conditional generative adversarial networks, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
